# xtool Core Guardrails

## Objectives
- Ensure stability by preventing regressions during incremental improvements.

## Generated Code
- Do **not** edit or refactor `src/main/generated/prisma-client/**` (including `runtime/library.d.ts`). It is produced by Prisma; changes are lost on `prisma generate`. Adjust `prisma/schema.prisma`, generator `output`, or wrap usage in app code (e.g. `prismaClient.ts`) instead.

## Mandatory Rules
- Maintain backward compatibility for existing API/IPC contracts.
- Apply changes in small, incremental diffs.
- Never revert existing logic without explicit rationale.
- Prioritize `appDefaults` for configuration presets.
- Respect strict boundaries between Main, Renderer, and Shared processes.
- Reuse common utility functions; avoid redundant I/O logic.

## Performance & UI
- Use lazy loading for heavy routes/panels.
- If performance regression is suspected, take the median of 3 measurements.